# Demo Structure

Each demo is a self-contained folder inside `demos/`:

```
demos/{demo-name}/
├── README.md              # Required
├── Dockerfile             # Required
├── {standard entrypoint}  # main.py, index.ts, main.rs, etc.
├── {deps file}            # Only if the demo has dependencies
└── {test file}            # At least one minimal test
```

## Requirements

- Entry point follows the language/framework standard naming (`main.py`, `index.ts`, `main.rs`, `Main.java`...)
- Dependency file only when needed (`requirements.txt`, `package.json`, `Cargo.toml`...)
- Every demo must include at least one test
- Every demo must include a Dockerfile to run in a container
